<h3 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites</h3>

<p>Run command located in package.json:</p>
<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>npm run setup
</code></pre></div></div>
<p>to install all of the required libraries</p>

<h3 id="installing">Installing</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Update API.js with your own <a href="https://github.com/athom031/UserRegLatLong/blob/master/API.js">API key</a>.</li>
  <li>Update the <a href="https://github.com/athom031/UserRegLatLong/blob/master/server/config/config.json">config file</a> in the server side on what is the link to the Mongo DB as the MONGO URI.</li>
  <li>Run the command to install all of the required libraries: <br />
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>npm run setup
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
  <li>This application runs on the following ports: <br />
    <ul>
      <li>PORT 3000 =&gt; backend <br /></li>
      <li>PORT 3001 =&gt; user registration/login front end <br /></li>
      <li>PORT 3002 =&gt; client user map front end <br />
if you have things running on those ports run the command to kill those local ports:
 <br /></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>npm run clear
</code></pre></div></div>

<ol>
  <li>Run the command to concurrently run the application (frontend and backend):
    <div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>"npm run dev" 
</code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

<h2 id="built-with">Built With</h2>
